{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KS7JzaTa65CeYVNC5xmPFy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pod is running and the HTTPS probe is working (it's getting a 503, which means CockroachDB started in secure mode, but the cluster might need to be initialized). The issue is that with TLS, the pods need to complete the cluster join. Pod 2 is returning 503 on the ready check.\n\nThe problem is that when switching from insecure to secure mode, existing data in persistent volumes might cause issues. Let me check what's happening with the CockroachDB logs.\n\nAlso, one big concern: CockroachDB nodes already have data from the insecure run. \n\nThe 503 on pod 2's readiness probe suggests it's still starting up rather than a fundamental configuration problem. Looking at the pod ages, pods 0 and 1 appear to be from the rolling update, so this might just be a timing issue as the cluster stabilizes with TLS enabled.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":788,"cache_read_input_tokens":36418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":788},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7cfb7196-3a2d-4069-92d8-23c00446a073","uuid":"f2e55133-08ad-41cb-a980-f762a8068144","request_id":"req_011Ccfhc8USzvF737VMGi4qJ"}
