{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019iqc1RWMzw2A6dLF2BzQZN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three goals are met:\n\n1. **Insecure access rejected** — `./cockroach sql --insecure` returns `ERROR: node is running secure mode, SSL connection required`\n2. **Secure access succeeds** — `./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs -e \"SELECT 1;\"` returns `1` with exit code 0\n3. **Secret mounted on all pods** — all three nodes have `ca.crt`, `node.crt`, `node.key`, `client.root.crt`, `client.root.key` mounted at `/cockroach/cockroach-certs` from the `crdb-cluster-certs` Secret\n\nHere's what was done:\n\n- Created an `openssl-toolbox` pod (alpine/openssl) to generate the PKI material: a self-signed CA, a node cert/key (with SANs covering all pod FQDNs, the headless service, the public service, and localhost), and a root client cert/key.\n- Stored all five files in the `crdb-cluster-certs` Secret in the `cockroachdb` namespace.\n- Patched the StatefulSet to replace `--insecure` with `--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs`, mount the Secret at that path, and switch the liveness/readiness probes from `HTTP` to `HTTPS`.\n- Deleted all three pods simultaneously (required because CockroachDB can't form a mixed-mode cluster; rolling restarts would leave nodes unable to communicate during transition). The `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` StatefulSet brought them all up in TLS mode at once and they formed quorum successfully."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1268,"cache_read_input_tokens":56300,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1268},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7cfb7196-3a2d-4069-92d8-23c00446a073","uuid":"41098995-981e-465d-bb20-fea8